It is remarkable in the Abiponian physicians that they cure every kind of disease with one and the same medicine. Let us examine their method of healing. They apply their lips to the part affected, and suck it, spitting after every suction. At intervals they draw-up their breath from the very bottom of their breast, and blovv upon that part of the body which is in pain. That blowing and sucking are alternately re- peated. If the whole body languishes, if it burns with malignant heat, if it is seized with measles or small-pox, four or five of these har- pies fly to suek and blovv it, one fastening his lips on the arm, another on the side, a third and fourth on the feet. If a child eries, or re- fuses the breast, the mother gives him to a juggler to be sucked.
